articles.title: Curiosity rover completes the 'toughest climb' on Mars - Interesting Engineering
articles.description: NASA's car-sized Curiosity rover has recently accomplished climbing Jau, one of Mars' most difficult terrains.
articles.content:
The Earth-based drivers do not move the rover in real-time, but rather follow a predetermined path laid out by 15 "rover planners."
